Bronco lay on thew ground, mech fluid slippig out of his back and 
shoulder. He thought he would just give up now, and die honourably. 
But a voice inside him told him to keep going.

Who speaks to me in my head?

It's me, Octociz, the one you kidnapped.

Witch!! Warlock!! You put me into a huge sleep. If you were physical 
I would kill you!

 I'm not, but I know someone who is. Get to your feet Bronco, and 
defeat the enemy.

Bronco stumbled to hsi feet, his rage blinding him. He saw the bot he 
fighting against with his back turned, busy with another bot. This is 
the best chance he'll get. He quietly crept up on the bot(Chordan) 
and placed his Rocket Launchers right up against his back. No warning 
this time.

Bronco pulled the triggers as fast as his battle worn fingers could.
